  "text": "The parallel texts for both language pairs are aligned using MTTK [CITATION_1] . We extract hierarchical rules from the aligned parallel texts using the constraints developed by [CITATION_2] . We further filter the extracted rules by count and pattern as described by [CITATION_3] . The following features are extracted from the parallel data and used to assign scores to translation rules: source-to-target and targetto-source phrase translation models, word and rule penalties, number of usages of the glue rule, source-to-target and target-to-source lexical models, and three rule count features inspired by [CITATION_4] .",
